Usage: set_quiet_attacker [-help] [-analysis_type {early late}]
                          [-attacker <string>] [-transition {rise fall}]
                          [-victim <string>] [-view <string>]

-help                           # Prints out the command usage
-analysis_type {early late}     # type (enum, optional)
-attacker <string>              # Specifies the attackers which should be made
                                # quiet for given victim net(s). If no attacker
                                # is specified, all the aggressors of given
                                # victim(s) will be ignored. (string, optional)
-transition {rise fall}         # Specifies the victim transition for which
                                # attackers will be assumed quiet. If no value
                                # is specified, attackers are skipped for both
                                # rise and fall transitions of the victim net.
                                # (enum, optional)
-victim <string>                # Specifies a list of victim nets for which
                                # attackers should be made quiet.
                                # (string, optional)
-view <string>                  # Specifies the view for which attackers should
                                # be made quiet. If no view is specified,
                                # attackers are assumed quiet in all views.
                                # (string, optional)